# 2004-07-01.iwj.1: Software Freedom Day

July 1st, 2004

The following resolution has been accepted by the Board of Directors
of Software in the Public Interest.

### Whereas

1. Software in the Public Interest promotes use and development of
   free software,
2. The Software Freedom Day is meant to celebrate Free and Open Source
   Software,
3. More information on the Software Freedom Day can be found at the
   website [www.softwarefreedomday.org](http://www.softwarefreedomday.org/)

### The Board resolves that

1. Software in the Public Interest fully supports the Software Freedom Day,

2. SPI encourages all its members to participate in said day

